{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778465762186,"sessionID":"ses_1eb33e7adffeXhKUUx3OuvPcFX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-b1bba4afc3e1b347","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"references_cache/PMID_8321236.md"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_8321236.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: reference_id: PMID:8321236\n3: title: The fission yeast ferric reductase gene frp1+ is required for ferric iron uptake and encodes a protein that is homologous to the gp91-phox subunit of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase.\n4: authors:\n5: - Roman DG\n6: - Dancis A\n7: - Anderson GJ\n8: - Klausner RD\n9: journal: Mol Cell Biol\n10: year: '1993'\n11: doi: 10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993\n12: keywords:\n13: - Alleles\n14: - Amino Acid Sequence\n15: - Animals\n16: - Base Sequence\n17: - Cattle\n18: - \"Cloning, Molecular\"\n19: - \"DNA, Fungal/isolation & purification\"\n20: - FMN Reductase\n21: - Ferric Compounds/metabolism\n22: - Ferrous Compounds/metabolism\n23: - \"Gene Expression Regulation, Fungal\"\n24: - Genetic Complementation Test\n25: - Humans\n26: - Molecular Sequence Data\n27: - Mutation\n28: - \"NADH, NADPH Oxidoreductases/chemistry, genetics, metabolism\"\n29: - Phagocytes/enzymology\n30: - \"Promoter Regions, Genetic\"\n31: - Restriction Mapping\n32: - \"Schizosaccharomyces/enzymology, genetics, growth & development\"\n33: - Sequence Homology\n34: - Substrate Specificity\n35: - \"Transcription, Genetic\"\n36: content_type: abstract_only\n37: ---\n38: \n39: # The fission yeast ferric reductase gene frp1+ is required for ferric iron uptake and encodes a protein that is homologous to the gp91-phox subunit of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase.\n40: **Authors:** Roman DG, Dancis A, Anderson GJ, Klausner RD\n41: **Journal:** Mol Cell Biol (1993)\n42: **DOI:** [10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993](https://doi.org/10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993)\n43: \n44: ## Content\n45: \n46: 1. Mol Cell Biol. 1993 Jul;13(7):4342-50. doi: 10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993.\n47: \n48: The fission yeast ferric reductase gene frp1+ is required for ferric iron uptake \n49: and encodes a protein that is homologous to the gp91-phox subunit of the human \n50: NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase.\n51: \n52: Roman DG(1), Dancis A, Anderson GJ, Klausner RD.\n53: \n54: Author information:\n55: (1)Cell Biology and Metabolism Branch, National Institute of Child Health and \n56: Human Development, Bethesda, Maryland 20892.\n57: \n58: We have identified a cell surface ferric reductase activity in the fission yeast \n59: Schizosaccharomyces pombe. A mutant strain deficient in this activity was also \n60: deficient in ferric iron uptake, while ferrous iron uptake was not impaired. \n61: Therefore, reduction is a required step in cellular ferric iron acquisition. We \n62: have cloned frp1+, the wild-type allele of the mutant gene. frp1+ mRNA levels \n63: were repressed by iron addition to the growth medium. Fusion of 138 nucleotides \n64: of frp1+ promoter sequences to a reporter gene, the bacterial chloramphenicol \n65: acetyltransferase gene, conferred iron-dependent regulation upon the latter when \n66: introduced into S. pombe. The predicted amino acid sequence of the frp1+ gene \n67: exhibits hydrophobic regions compatible with transmembrane domains. It shows \n68: similarity to the Saccharomyces cerevisiae FRE1 gene product and the gp91-phox \n69: protein, a component of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase that is \n70: deficient in X-linked chronic granulomatous disease.\n71: \n72: DOI: 10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993\n73: PMCID: PMC359993\n74: PMID: 8321236 [Indexed for MEDLINE]\n\n(End of file - total 74 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nreference_id: PMID:8321236\ntitle: The fission yeast ferric reductase gene frp1+ is required for ferric iron uptake and encodes a protein that is homologous to the gp91-phox subunit of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase.\nauthors:\n- Roman DG\n- Dancis A\n- Anderson GJ\n- Klausner RD\njournal: Mol Cell Biol\nyear: '1993'\ndoi: 10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993\nkeywords:\n- Alleles\n- Amino Acid Sequence\n- Animals\n- Base Sequence\n- Cattle\n- \"Cloning, Molecular\"\n- \"DNA, Fungal/isolation & purification\"\n- FMN Reductase","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"references_cache/PMID_8321236.md","time":{"start":1778465762177,"end":1778465762185}},"id":"prt_e14d1ddfc001s2Q0KsSZFp2ZHH","sessionID":"ses_1eb33e7adffeXhKUUx3OuvPcFX","messageID":"msg_e14d1d6f80015jM4P9JCa7fzE1"}}
